solutions.Solution 1:
Note that:


\begin{itemize}
\item Truth-tellers would answer yes-no-no to the three questions in this order.
\end{itemize}
\begin{itemize}
\item Liars would answer yes-yes-no to the three questions in this order.
\end{itemize}
\begin{itemize}
\item Alternaters who responded truth-lie-truth would answer no-no-no to the three questions in this order.
\end{itemize}
\begin{itemize}
\item Alternaters who responded lie-truth-lie would answer yes-yes-yes to the three questions in this order.
\end{itemize}
Suppose that there are $T$ truth-tellers, $L$ liars, and $A$ alternaters who responded lie-truth-lie.


The conditions of the first two questions imply that
\begin{align*} T+L+A&=22, \\ L+A&=15. \end{align*}
Subtracting the second equation from the first, we have $T=22-15=\boxed{\textbf{(A) } 7}.$


\underline{\textbf{Remark}}


The condition of the third question is extraneous. However, we know that there are $9$ alternaters who responded lie-truth-lie, $6$ liars, and $9$ alternaters who responded truth-lie-truth from this condition.


